1
00:01:06,066 --> 00:01:07,795
I want that shoulder.

2
00:01:07,834 --> 00:01:08,994
You want more?

3
00:01:30,123 --> 00:01:31,954
All right.

4
00:01:31,991 --> 00:01:33,219
Pat's waiting down there.

5
00:01:36,196 --> 00:01:37,857
Your brother can wait.

6
00:01:37,897 --> 00:01:39,831
He gets to see you
this entire holiday.

7
00:01:39,866 --> 00:01:41,163
I told you, Hope.

8
00:01:41,201 --> 00:01:42,634
I'll drive up
to Marin Christmas Night.

9
00:01:42,669 --> 00:01:45,536
Okay? Promise.
Nothing will stop me.

10
00:01:56,483 --> 00:01:57,814
Like every Christmas story...

11
00:01:57,851 --> 00:02:00,115
this one's about new life
in the dead of winter...

12
00:02:02,288 --> 00:02:04,188
but I didn't know that
at the time.

13
00:02:04,224 --> 00:02:05,816
I was just a college kid...

14
00:02:05,859 --> 00:02:08,589
coming home for vacation
with my brother Pat.

15
00:02:08,628 --> 00:02:10,562
It was 1977.

16
00:02:10,597 --> 00:02:11,825
My hometown of Placerville...

17
00:02:11,865 --> 00:02:14,129
is up in the foothills
of the High Sierra.

18
00:02:14,167 --> 00:02:17,227
It's not that far from Berkeley
as the crow flies.

19
00:02:17,270 --> 00:02:20,239
It was just another world away
for me.

20
00:02:44,230 --> 00:02:47,063
You see, Christmas
in Placerville never changed.

21
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:50,263
Every year, I painted the
scenery for the church pageant.

22
00:02:50,303 --> 00:02:52,669
And every year,
Mom took the children's choir...

23
00:02:52,705 --> 00:02:55,003
up to the mountains to listen
to the wind in the trees.

24
00:02:56,309 --> 00:02:58,106
What are you doing here?

25
00:02:58,144 --> 00:03:01,511
Oh, my beautiful boys.

26
00:03:23,803 --> 00:03:25,896
Our neighbor, Mr. Rosa...

27
00:03:25,939 --> 00:03:27,736
knew every shred of gossip
in town.

28
00:03:28,441 --> 00:03:29,465
Jupiter!

29
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:32,037
He's German, you know!

30
00:03:36,182 --> 00:03:38,878
Jupiter, stop kissing Tom.

31
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:42,117
Hi, Mr. Rosa. Thanks.

32
00:03:42,155 --> 00:03:43,952
Tom. Here, Pat.

33
00:03:43,990 --> 00:03:45,355
How are ya?

34
00:03:45,391 --> 00:03:46,881
I'll get that thing
running yet, Maryanne.

35
00:03:46,926 --> 00:03:48,791
I'll go look at it.

36
00:03:49,996 --> 00:03:51,861
You should know,
that big Thanksgiving rain...

37
00:03:51,898 --> 00:03:53,422
my house weathered fine.

38
00:03:53,466 --> 00:03:54,797
I keep it in mint condition.

39
00:03:54,834 --> 00:03:56,199
It's all in the upkeep.

40
00:03:56,236 --> 00:03:58,704
But your mom, the roof
leaked something terrible.

41
00:03:58,738 --> 00:04:00,069
Then the water pipe froze.

42
00:04:00,106 --> 00:04:01,733
It burst and...

43
00:04:01,774 --> 00:04:03,002
Water damage, huh?

44
00:04:03,042 --> 00:04:04,566
She didn't tell us.

45
00:04:04,611 --> 00:04:07,079
Maryanne wouldn't have told you.

46
00:04:07,113 --> 00:04:08,512
You know how your mother is.

47
00:04:08,548 --> 00:04:10,641
Yeah. You know what?
Thanks for sharing, Mr. Rosa.

48
00:04:10,683 --> 00:04:12,674
You know,
with you boys off at school...

49
00:04:12,719 --> 00:04:14,812
and then she's all alone...

50
00:04:14,854 --> 00:04:16,321
but she still teaches
the kids how to sing...

51
00:04:16,356 --> 00:04:18,517
and she sews all the Christmas
pageant costumes...

52
00:04:18,558 --> 00:04:20,651
and, oh,
she's got pep, your mom.

53
00:04:20,693 --> 00:04:22,183
Yeah, mucho pep.

54
00:04:22,228 --> 00:04:24,856
You boys should get
on the stick for her.

55
00:04:24,897 --> 00:04:26,262
She doesn't spill her own beans.

56
00:04:26,299 --> 00:04:28,529
So you spill them for me.

57
00:04:28,568 --> 00:04:30,968
Well, it needs oil
for one thing.

58
00:04:31,004 --> 00:04:32,062
You know, Mr. Rosa...

59
00:04:32,105 --> 00:04:33,970
if you ever did get
the truck fixed...

60
00:04:34,007 --> 00:04:35,998
you wouldn't have anything
to gossip about, would you?

61
00:04:36,042 --> 00:04:39,273
Come on, guys. I gotta
get supper over to Glen.

62
00:04:39,312 --> 00:04:40,870
- Thanks, Mr. Rosa.
- See ya, Mr. Rosa.

63
00:04:44,684 --> 00:04:47,482
Sometimes life
moves in mysterious ways...

64
00:04:47,520 --> 00:04:50,785
and sometimes
there's no mystery at all...

65
00:04:50,823 --> 00:04:52,984
like when Glen Wesman
built his studio...

66
00:04:53,026 --> 00:04:54,015
across the field from us.

67
00:04:55,161 --> 00:04:56,992
Having a famous artist
next door...

68
00:04:57,030 --> 00:05:00,397
was like God's finger
pointing me toward painting.

69
00:05:00,433 --> 00:05:01,798
All through high school...

70
00:05:01,834 --> 00:05:03,802
Glen taught me what it means
to be an artist.

71
00:05:04,937 --> 00:05:05,926
Glen?

72
00:05:05,972 --> 00:05:09,032
Close the damn door.

73
00:05:11,311 --> 00:05:12,676
Glen, it's Tom.

74
00:05:12,712 --> 00:05:14,009
It's cold in here.

75
00:05:14,047 --> 00:05:17,483
Why would you leave
the door open?

76
00:05:17,517 --> 00:05:19,007
Where on earth are you?

77
00:05:19,052 --> 00:05:21,384
In the corner...

78
00:05:21,421 --> 00:05:23,753
like Little Jack Horner.

79
00:05:23,790 --> 00:05:24,950
What?

80
00:05:24,991 --> 00:05:26,549
Come in.

81
00:05:27,994 --> 00:05:30,292
I'm learning Latin.

82
00:05:30,330 --> 00:05:33,629
A dead language...

83
00:05:33,666 --> 00:05:35,133
for the dead.

84
00:05:38,938 --> 00:05:40,963
Maleficent crap, eh?

85
00:05:42,575 --> 00:05:43,564
They're not done.

86
00:05:43,609 --> 00:05:46,510
Some things are
better left undone.

87
00:05:48,448 --> 00:05:50,109
I can't capture her.

88
00:05:51,317 --> 00:05:56,050
Can't paint the loss.
My hands won't cooperate.

89
00:05:57,056 --> 00:05:59,115
Don't get old.

90
00:06:00,827 --> 00:06:05,526
That's the sum of my wisdom
at this advanced age.

91
00:06:05,565 --> 00:06:07,931
Don't get old.

92
00:06:09,802 --> 00:06:10,632
Don't...

93
00:06:12,271 --> 00:06:13,101
get...

94
00:06:14,173 --> 00:06:17,802
Oh, damned hand.

95
00:06:17,844 --> 00:06:20,335
Nothing works
the way it used to.

96
00:06:22,849 --> 00:06:23,838
Let me get that.

97
00:06:25,451 --> 00:06:26,645
- Write.
- Yup.

98
00:06:26,686 --> 00:06:28,950
"Don't get old."

99
00:06:29,989 --> 00:06:30,978
Pin it up.

100
00:06:33,393 --> 00:06:34,724
How's your work?

101
00:06:34,761 --> 00:06:37,195
I'd like to see what
you've been painting.

102
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:39,289
I feel lost, really.

103
00:06:39,332 --> 00:06:40,162
Here.

104
00:06:40,366 --> 00:06:42,357
'Cause I've been doing
a lot of, uh...

105
00:06:43,736 --> 00:06:46,569
a lot of
expressionistic stuff lately.

106
00:06:46,606 --> 00:06:48,733
That will get you lost
very quickly.

107
00:06:48,775 --> 00:06:52,734
Don't reduce art to something
that's about the artist.

108
00:06:52,779 --> 00:06:54,337
Art isn't about the artist.

109
00:06:54,380 --> 00:06:55,312
It's about life.

110
00:06:56,449 --> 00:06:57,677
Life...

111
00:06:59,085 --> 00:07:00,677
beauty...

112
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:02,085
Iove...

113
00:07:02,121 --> 00:07:04,146
emotion.

114
00:07:04,190 --> 00:07:08,388
Art should bring emotion
that can topple tyranny.

115
00:07:08,428 --> 00:07:10,589
I haven't forgotten, Glen.

116
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:15,561
Are you gonna try
this one again?

117
00:07:16,869 --> 00:07:19,667
We were in Paris
before the war.

118
00:07:21,641 --> 00:07:24,667
And we would picnic
along the Seine.

119
00:07:24,710 --> 00:07:26,041
You and Nicole?

120
00:07:26,078 --> 00:07:30,674
A little wine, some bread
by the water.

121
00:07:30,716 --> 00:07:33,446
She liked the simple things.

122
00:07:34,687 --> 00:07:38,453
I lay back on the grass
and looked up.

123
00:07:38,491 --> 00:07:41,688
The light played
through the trees...

124
00:07:41,727 --> 00:07:43,354
touched her.

125
00:07:44,764 --> 00:07:48,700
You must see
the summer light in Paris.

126
00:07:48,734 --> 00:07:53,467
It surrounds the leaves,
holds them somehow.

127
00:07:53,506 --> 00:07:55,098
If there were a God...

128
00:07:55,141 --> 00:07:57,575
that light
would be like his hand...

129
00:07:57,610 --> 00:08:00,841
holding the whole world
together.

130
00:08:00,880 --> 00:08:03,041
If I could paint that...

131
00:08:03,082 --> 00:08:05,141
Yeah, I bet that art dealer
in San Francisco...

132
00:08:05,184 --> 00:08:06,310
would be very happy.

133
00:08:06,352 --> 00:08:08,183
Sidney.

134
00:08:08,221 --> 00:08:11,122
You know, a new Glen Wesman
would be worth a lot of money.

135
00:08:11,157 --> 00:08:15,287
Sidney always tries
to inspire me.

136
00:08:16,496 --> 00:08:19,624
"Call Sidney.

137
00:08:21,734 --> 00:08:27,138
"Tell him to go to hell."

138
00:08:29,342 --> 00:08:30,502
You like Sidney.

139
00:08:33,746 --> 00:08:34,770
Do I?

140
00:08:34,814 --> 00:08:37,783
You always said you did.

141
00:08:39,318 --> 00:08:41,149
What was I writing?

142
00:08:41,187 --> 00:08:43,155
You know, don't even...

143
00:08:43,189 --> 00:08:44,884
Don't even bother
writing it down, Glen.

144
00:08:46,659 --> 00:08:48,058
I bet you'll remember
to tell him to go to hell...

145
00:08:48,094 --> 00:08:49,083
when you see him.

146
00:08:49,128 --> 00:08:50,356
Yes.

147
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:56,794
I shall recline here
like an Oriental potentate...

148
00:08:58,504 --> 00:09:03,840
and then try once again
to capture Nicole...

149
00:09:05,144 --> 00:09:07,237
record the loss.

150
00:09:09,882 --> 00:09:10,712
Nicole...

151
00:09:23,963 --> 00:09:25,396
Want to top things off
with tea?

152
00:09:25,431 --> 00:09:27,592
Fresca?
Some other fine beverage?

153
00:09:27,633 --> 00:09:28,622
No.

154
00:09:29,869 --> 00:09:31,029
FINAL NOTICE

155
00:09:32,305 --> 00:09:33,363
Mom, what is this?

156
00:09:37,710 --> 00:09:40,440
- Nothing.
- Nothing?

157
00:09:40,479 --> 00:09:42,208
Bank says they're
foreclosing, Mom.

158
00:09:42,248 --> 00:09:45,547
Tom, this is my business,
not yours.

159
00:09:45,585 --> 00:09:46,779
Let me see.

160
00:09:49,188 --> 00:09:50,382
I'll figure it out.

161
00:09:50,423 --> 00:09:51,890
I have until New Year's...

162
00:09:51,924 --> 00:09:53,221
to come up with
the back payments.

163
00:09:53,259 --> 00:09:56,387
$3,151...

164
00:09:56,429 --> 00:09:57,521
and 39 cents.

165
00:09:58,698 --> 00:10:01,258
This is due in two weeks.

166
00:10:01,300 --> 00:10:02,426
How can they do this?

167
00:10:02,468 --> 00:10:06,268
They have already
extended me countless times.

168
00:10:06,305 --> 00:10:07,602
I've spoken to them.

169
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:09,904
There's nothing more
they can do.

170
00:10:09,942 --> 00:10:12,342
Mom, how could you
fall this far behind?

171
00:10:12,378 --> 00:10:13,868
Why didn't you tell us, Mom?

172
00:10:13,913 --> 00:10:14,743
Stop.

173
00:10:15,781 --> 00:10:17,544
You are my boys.

174
00:10:17,583 --> 00:10:20,143
I'm supposed
to take care of you...

175
00:10:20,186 --> 00:10:21,813
not the other way around.

176
00:10:25,124 --> 00:10:26,614
We're gonna lose the cottage.

177
00:10:39,338 --> 00:10:40,862
Tom?

178
00:10:40,906 --> 00:10:42,897
Oh, I was so close
to being asleep.

179
00:10:45,344 --> 00:10:46,368
No, you weren't.

180
00:10:46,412 --> 00:10:49,176
Okay. I wasn't.

181
00:10:50,349 --> 00:10:52,249
You know how
I used to fall asleep?

182
00:10:56,656 --> 00:10:58,521
It was looking
at that drawing of Dad...

183
00:11:03,963 --> 00:11:06,261
and dreaming about
when he'd come back.

184
00:11:08,434 --> 00:11:09,264
Babies.

185
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:12,262
On her own.

186
00:11:16,242 --> 00:11:19,006
I remember Mom told me
I was the man of the house.

187
00:11:25,551 --> 00:11:27,280
I'm not gonna go see Hope.

188
00:11:31,057 --> 00:11:32,957
I'm gonna stay here
and get a job...

189
00:11:32,992 --> 00:11:34,289
and work over the break.

190
00:11:35,695 --> 00:11:37,754
You and Hope are like...

191
00:11:37,797 --> 00:11:39,287
pretty serious?

192
00:11:39,331 --> 00:11:40,457
She'll have to understand.

193
00:11:41,634 --> 00:11:43,192
We can't leave Mom like this.

194
00:11:46,205 --> 00:11:47,467
Yeah, okay.

195
00:11:47,506 --> 00:11:49,064
Me, too.
I'll find something, too.

196
00:11:49,108 --> 00:11:49,938
Some job.

197
00:11:50,876 --> 00:11:54,107
Yeah. Good.

198
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:01,846
Trade ya.

199
00:12:04,457 --> 00:12:06,755
You're on vacation.

200
00:12:06,792 --> 00:12:08,282
You shouldn't be getting jobs.

201
00:12:08,327 --> 00:12:09,885
Yeah, but, Mom, you have a job.

202
00:12:09,929 --> 00:12:11,954
You go to work every day.
Why shouldn't we?

203
00:12:11,997 --> 00:12:13,362
This isn't right.

204
00:12:13,399 --> 00:12:14,923
Living like this?

205
00:12:14,967 --> 00:12:15,956
You need help.

206
00:12:16,001 --> 00:12:19,767
No. Your job is
to focus on school...

207
00:12:19,805 --> 00:12:21,796
and when you come home,
you're on vacation.

208
00:12:22,508 --> 00:12:23,532
So...

209
00:12:25,144 --> 00:12:27,544
relax. Enjoy yourselves.

210
00:12:33,619 --> 00:12:35,314
Pancakes, anyone?

211
00:12:44,463 --> 00:12:45,794
Blue box.

212
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:49,434
Thanks for the job, Big Jim.

213
00:12:49,468 --> 00:12:51,026
I don't know much
about electricity...

214
00:12:51,070 --> 00:12:52,128
but I'm gonna work real hard.

215
00:12:52,171 --> 00:12:53,638
Well, we're gonna
have to, Pat...

216
00:12:53,672 --> 00:12:56,641
because these people
over here never sleep.

217
00:12:56,675 --> 00:13:01,237
I gotta tell ya, they've been
trying to top me for 25 years.

218
00:13:15,761 --> 00:13:16,887
Your move, Big Jim.

219
00:13:17,129 --> 00:13:19,393
You're pathetic, Gunderson!

220
00:13:19,431 --> 00:13:22,696
You and your uptight,
beady-eyed wife!

221
00:13:22,735 --> 00:13:24,566
You think you can top me?

222
00:13:24,603 --> 00:13:26,867
I'm Mr. Electricity
in this town.

223
00:13:26,906 --> 00:13:28,134
Watch this.

224
00:13:28,174 --> 00:13:30,608
I built this myself, Pat.

225
00:13:44,590 --> 00:13:46,285
Does that go any faster?

226
00:13:47,259 --> 00:13:48,248
No.

227
00:13:50,162 --> 00:13:52,096
Don't give in to him.

228
00:13:52,131 --> 00:13:55,225
He called me beady-eyed
in front of the neighbors.

229
00:14:10,783 --> 00:14:13,274
Right there,
that's why I need your help.

230
00:14:17,056 --> 00:14:19,388
They're bitter,
ugly people, Pat.

231
00:14:19,425 --> 00:14:21,086
Sadists at heart.

232
00:14:21,126 --> 00:14:24,220
Keep your cat off my yard!

233
00:14:24,263 --> 00:14:26,823
I found a hairball
in my manger!

234
00:14:26,866 --> 00:14:28,163
You don't have a manger!

235
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:30,259
Yeah, you don't have a manger.

236
00:14:30,302 --> 00:14:31,428
I hate that cat.

237
00:14:32,471 --> 00:14:34,598
Come on, let's go
blow up Mrs. Claus.

238
00:14:35,841 --> 00:14:37,433
I do too have a manger.

239
00:14:37,476 --> 00:14:38,943
I got everything.

240
00:15:03,135 --> 00:15:04,727
Ernie, hey.

241
00:15:04,770 --> 00:15:05,600
Hey.

242
00:15:05,804 --> 00:15:06,828
Little Thomas Kinkade...

243
00:15:06,872 --> 00:15:08,362
all the way from college.

244
00:15:08,407 --> 00:15:09,339
Look at you.

245
00:15:09,441 --> 00:15:10,772
Jeez.

246
00:15:10,809 --> 00:15:12,071
Take a seat.

247
00:15:12,111 --> 00:15:13,476
Give this man
a Pepsi-Cola, will ya?

248
00:15:13,512 --> 00:15:14,501
Sure.

249
00:15:14,546 --> 00:15:16,537
Thanks. You know, um...

250
00:15:16,582 --> 00:15:17,571
I was actually
looking for you...

251
00:15:17,616 --> 00:15:20,141
because I wanted to talk to you
about finding a job.

252
00:15:20,185 --> 00:15:21,880
You know, just something
over the holidays.

253
00:15:21,921 --> 00:15:22,979
A job, huh?

254
00:15:23,022 --> 00:15:25,320
- Yeah.
- Right, work.

255
00:15:25,357 --> 00:15:26,824
- Yeah.
- Employment.

256
00:15:26,859 --> 00:15:29,885
You're in Placerville, son,
and I can tell...

257
00:15:29,929 --> 00:15:31,396
you're digging for gold,
aren't ya?

258
00:15:32,598 --> 00:15:33,929
Let me tell you something.

259
00:15:33,966 --> 00:15:35,331
I'm digging for gold, too.

260
00:15:36,235 --> 00:15:38,135
Tourist gold.

261
00:15:39,638 --> 00:15:41,503
Who do you think's gonna buy
the Haggar slacks...

262
00:15:41,540 --> 00:15:42,666
at the Round Tent?

263
00:15:42,708 --> 00:15:45,302
Who's gonna buy
the cowboy hats at Arian's?

264
00:15:45,344 --> 00:15:47,107
Any thoughts?

265
00:15:47,146 --> 00:15:48,545
Tourists.

266
00:15:48,580 --> 00:15:50,411
Tourists, exactly.

267
00:15:50,449 --> 00:15:53,350
But tourists who are
gonna be coming...

268
00:15:53,385 --> 00:15:57,845
to the Christmas tree
capital of the world, baby.

269
00:15:57,890 --> 00:15:59,585
Yeah, sounds good. So...

270
00:15:59,625 --> 00:16:00,717
Sounds good? No, no, no.

271
