796
00:46:18,442 --> 00:46:23,436
Every year, Marc Chagall
yelled at me, huh?

797
00:46:23,480 --> 00:46:25,004
Said he'd never paint again.

798
00:46:25,048 --> 00:46:29,007
But he always came up
with a new piece from inside.

799
00:46:29,052 --> 00:46:31,919
And you can do the same.

800
00:46:37,094 --> 00:46:39,927
I've been trying
for months to do it, Sid.

801
00:46:41,799 --> 00:46:43,323
To capture Nicole...

802
00:46:43,367 --> 00:46:45,665
so the world would
never lose her.

803
00:46:49,606 --> 00:46:51,904
It's not there.

804
00:46:53,911 --> 00:46:57,142
I may not live
to see Christmas.

805
00:47:11,328 --> 00:47:13,091
Get to work.

806
00:47:14,965 --> 00:47:16,455
As you leave...

807
00:47:16,500 --> 00:47:18,525
I'm leaving? I just got here.

808
00:47:18,569 --> 00:47:22,061
Your inspiration
has exhausted me.

809
00:47:22,105 --> 00:47:23,970
As you leave...

810
00:47:24,007 --> 00:47:26,976
would you please
bring me my staff?

811
00:47:27,010 --> 00:47:28,477
My rod.

812
00:47:28,512 --> 00:47:30,742
I'll do that.

813
00:47:30,781 --> 00:47:34,410
Somehow this walker
has appeared by my bed...

814
00:47:34,451 --> 00:47:36,316
and I don't want
the damn thing.

815
00:47:37,588 --> 00:47:38,850
Uh, Your Worship.

816
00:47:43,327 --> 00:47:44,817
Now you can go to hell.

817
00:47:58,976 --> 00:47:59,806
Nicole...

818
00:48:02,079 --> 00:48:03,808
Nicole...

819
00:48:06,383 --> 00:48:08,647
Those pictures
are unsaleable.

820
00:48:08,685 --> 00:48:09,674
They're not finished.

821
00:48:09,720 --> 00:48:11,984
They are finished.

822
00:48:16,226 --> 00:48:17,750
He won't go back
and finish them...

823
00:48:17,794 --> 00:48:18,920
and he knows it.

824
00:48:21,565 --> 00:48:23,692
He's been depressed
ever since Nicole died...

825
00:48:25,235 --> 00:48:27,499
and it's gotten
in the way of his genius.

826
00:48:28,906 --> 00:48:30,237
It's worse than that.

827
00:48:31,909 --> 00:48:34,139
He's been getting
confused lately.

828
00:48:38,815 --> 00:48:42,342
He has one more painting in him.

829
00:48:42,386 --> 00:48:44,217
I'm sure of it.

830
00:48:44,254 --> 00:48:46,552
That would make your bank
account very happy, I'm sure.

831
00:48:50,427 --> 00:48:53,658
I know you think
I'm some kind of mercenary.

832
00:48:53,697 --> 00:48:55,528
That's my job.

833
00:48:55,565 --> 00:48:59,695
I love Glen.
I love his art, too.

834
00:48:59,736 --> 00:49:03,502
And I've done right by him
for a long time.

835
00:49:03,540 --> 00:49:07,271
And he's done
a hell of a lot for you.

836
00:49:10,147 --> 00:49:11,136
So...

837
00:49:12,849 --> 00:49:13,975
how's life treating you?

838
00:49:16,420 --> 00:49:18,081
Have you got a minute,
Mr. Marvin?

839
00:49:27,397 --> 00:49:28,489
My family...

840
00:49:31,134 --> 00:49:32,567
we're...

841
00:49:32,602 --> 00:49:34,229
We're in a bit
of a financial pinch.

842
00:49:36,606 --> 00:49:37,732
Do you think maybe...

843
00:49:39,776 --> 00:49:41,209
Do you think maybe
there'd ever be a buyer...

844
00:49:41,244 --> 00:49:42,404
for any of these?

845
00:50:01,999 --> 00:50:03,125
I don't think so.

846
00:50:04,368 --> 00:50:08,168
Your teachers at Berkeley
do this kind of thing better.

847
00:50:08,205 --> 00:50:10,435
These are pale imitations.

848
00:50:10,474 --> 00:50:11,463
I'm sorry.

849
00:50:13,176 --> 00:50:15,644
You might have something
inside you.

850
00:50:17,581 --> 00:50:20,744
I don't think
you've found it yet.

851
00:50:24,855 --> 00:50:26,686
But you sure as hell
can draw.

852
00:50:44,541 --> 00:50:45,701
It's beautiful.

853
00:50:48,011 --> 00:50:49,376
It's this little town and...

854
00:50:51,381 --> 00:50:53,144
these people
I've known all my life.

855
00:50:55,652 --> 00:50:57,517
There's so much love here.

856
00:51:01,058 --> 00:51:03,288
It's beautiful, Tom.

857
00:51:03,326 --> 00:51:05,351
Don't ever doubt that.

858
00:51:05,395 --> 00:51:06,794
Nanette was my first love.

859
00:51:07,798 --> 00:51:09,561
I hadn't seen her
in almost a year.

860
00:51:11,234 --> 00:51:12,826
Funny how my heart jumped.

861
00:51:14,171 --> 00:51:15,297
Five...

862
00:51:15,338 --> 00:51:16,430
four...

863
00:51:16,473 --> 00:51:17,735
three, two...

864
00:51:17,774 --> 00:51:18,763
one.

865
00:51:22,112 --> 00:51:23,670
Oh, that's so tacky.

866
00:51:23,713 --> 00:51:26,409
Take that, Gunderson.

867
00:51:34,825 --> 00:51:36,053
Keep them lights
a-coming, Patrick.

868
00:51:36,093 --> 00:51:37,583
You're doing great there, boy.

869
00:51:48,338 --> 00:51:50,033
What do you want
to do today, Vesta?

870
00:51:51,007 --> 00:51:52,269
Look, there we are.

871
00:51:52,309 --> 00:51:53,901
Hi, Butch.

872
00:51:53,944 --> 00:51:55,775
Mother's milk.

873
00:51:57,280 --> 00:51:58,770
Right back at ya.

874
00:52:05,655 --> 00:52:07,384
If we could just start.

875
00:52:09,926 --> 00:52:11,018
Mr. Chang.

876
00:52:12,095 --> 00:52:13,323
Gunderson...

877
00:52:15,699 --> 00:52:19,897
the wind is blowing down
your elves.

878
00:52:19,936 --> 00:52:21,403
What wind?

879
00:52:21,438 --> 00:52:24,805
And your flocking stinks.

880
00:52:24,841 --> 00:52:28,242
Your flocking is outstanding.

881
00:52:30,680 --> 00:52:33,877
You can bring love
into our church pageant...

882
00:52:33,917 --> 00:52:37,114
but you have to hear it
and feel it first.

883
00:52:48,932 --> 00:52:50,229
Am I beautiful?

884
00:52:52,102 --> 00:52:53,126
I thought so.

885
00:52:56,740 --> 00:52:58,002
It's coming along, huh?

886
00:52:59,309 --> 00:53:01,174
Gunderson.

887
00:53:04,114 --> 00:53:05,979
Yeah.

888
00:53:08,218 --> 00:53:10,186
Merry Christmas there, Butch.

889
00:53:18,161 --> 00:53:19,492
January 5th.

890
00:53:24,768 --> 00:53:26,201
I don't know, Kinkade.

891
00:53:26,236 --> 00:53:27,760
I mean, it's, uh...

892
00:53:27,804 --> 00:53:29,101
Well, it's interesting.

893
00:53:29,906 --> 00:53:30,964
No, it's not.

894
00:53:32,642 --> 00:53:34,337
It's not gonna work.

895
00:53:34,377 --> 00:53:37,972
Hey. There's my store.

896
00:53:38,014 --> 00:53:40,983
Wow. Very beautiful.

897
00:53:41,017 --> 00:53:43,144
I like that very much.

898
00:53:43,186 --> 00:53:44,710
See? He hates it.

899
00:53:44,754 --> 00:53:45,778
Oh, well.

900
00:53:45,822 --> 00:53:47,346
That's me...

901
00:53:48,391 --> 00:53:49,380
with Jupiter.

902
00:53:49,426 --> 00:53:51,519
You see how friendly he is?
I told ya, Tom.

903
00:53:51,561 --> 00:53:53,654
Look how skinny I am.

904
00:53:53,697 --> 00:53:56,165
You know,
it was actually my idea...

905
00:53:56,199 --> 00:53:57,996
to have him paint the people...

906
00:53:58,034 --> 00:54:00,127
that make Placerville
so special.

907
00:54:00,170 --> 00:54:01,637
I may not know much
about artwork...

908
00:54:01,671 --> 00:54:03,798
but I do know
what the public wants.

909
00:54:05,041 --> 00:54:07,305
Very beautiful.

910
00:54:07,344 --> 00:54:09,175
You ready to take
a break there, Tom, huh?

911
00:54:09,212 --> 00:54:10,941
A break? No.

912
00:54:10,981 --> 00:54:12,573
Day after tomorrow's
Christmas Eve.

913
00:54:12,616 --> 00:54:14,914
This has to be ready
for the TV cameras.

914
00:54:14,951 --> 00:54:17,715
No, you can take a break
after Christmas. Yeah?

915
00:54:18,922 --> 00:54:20,355
Listen, fifty bucks...

916
00:54:20,390 --> 00:54:22,824
if you can find a spot
to put me in there, huh?

917
00:54:22,859 --> 00:54:25,350
Fifty? Yeah?

918
00:54:25,395 --> 00:54:26,760
Forty-five. Just paint me in.

919
00:54:27,097 --> 00:54:28,086
Okay, great.

920
00:54:28,131 --> 00:54:29,257
Wonderful.

921
00:54:33,737 --> 00:54:35,102
Big Jim gave me some overtime.

922
00:54:37,407 --> 00:54:40,843
And I'll have 500,
assuming I can finish the mural.

923
00:54:42,545 --> 00:54:44,706
Then there's about 200
in my savings account.

924
00:54:44,748 --> 00:54:46,807
I must have a hundred or so.

925
00:54:48,618 --> 00:54:50,176
That leaves us short.

926
00:54:59,596 --> 00:55:00,585
Hello.

927
00:55:00,630 --> 00:55:02,530
I'm looking at you right now.

928
00:55:02,565 --> 00:55:03,827
Hi.

929
00:55:03,867 --> 00:55:05,027
At one of your paintings.

930
00:55:05,902 --> 00:55:06,891
Hope.

931
00:55:06,936 --> 00:55:10,099
I miss you so much, Thomas.

932
00:55:11,608 --> 00:55:12,836
Yeah, me, too.

933
00:55:12,876 --> 00:55:15,572
And I decided,
if you can't come to me...

934
00:55:16,713 --> 00:55:17,907
I'll come to you.

935
00:55:36,466 --> 00:55:38,058
Dad.

936
00:55:38,101 --> 00:55:39,398
Number one son!

937
00:55:41,438 --> 00:55:42,735
Park yourself right there.

938
00:55:42,772 --> 00:55:45,400
Join me at the altar, Tommy.

939
00:55:48,211 --> 00:55:50,406
What I'm most proud about you,
T-Bone...

940
00:55:51,381 --> 00:55:52,905
T-Boneus Rex...

941
00:55:56,119 --> 00:55:58,053
is that you
never took up smoking.

942
00:55:59,923 --> 00:56:01,288
I'm really proud about that.

943
00:56:04,728 --> 00:56:06,787
Look, Dad, I have
to talk to you about Mom.

944
00:56:06,830 --> 00:56:08,923
Right, yeah. I remember.

945
00:56:08,965 --> 00:56:10,762
You mentioned the, uh...

946
00:56:12,068 --> 00:56:13,092
The money.

947
00:56:19,242 --> 00:56:20,641
See, Mom got behind.

948
00:56:20,677 --> 00:56:22,975
Oh, she got behind, did she?

949
00:56:23,012 --> 00:56:24,240
Well, there's the switch.

950
00:56:25,281 --> 00:56:27,078
She was always and forever
grinding my gears...

951
00:56:27,117 --> 00:56:28,448
about getting behind.

952
00:56:28,485 --> 00:56:31,283
Now she's behind.

953
00:56:33,289 --> 00:56:37,851
That, number one son,
I find a regular laugh riot.

954
00:56:37,894 --> 00:56:39,225
Well, it's not funny.

955
00:56:41,564 --> 00:56:43,156
We're gonna lose
the cottage, Dad.

956
00:56:43,967 --> 00:56:45,730
We gotta come up with $3,000.

957
00:56:48,171 --> 00:56:49,160
Three grand.

958
00:56:50,974 --> 00:56:52,498
Big spender, your mother.

959
00:56:52,542 --> 00:56:54,942
Look, Dad, she...

960
00:56:54,978 --> 00:56:56,741
She loaned people money, okay?

961
00:56:56,780 --> 00:56:57,940
She gave people things.

962
00:56:57,981 --> 00:57:00,506
She never gave me a dime.

963
00:57:01,684 --> 00:57:02,776
Well, couldn't...

964
00:57:04,687 --> 00:57:05,847
Couldn't you for me?

965
00:57:08,291 --> 00:57:09,588
For Pat?

966
00:57:15,064 --> 00:57:16,224
Well, you see, kiddo...

967
00:57:19,035 --> 00:57:20,161
number one son...

968
00:57:22,572 --> 00:57:23,561
I ain't got it.

969
00:57:27,177 --> 00:57:32,672
I'm livin' paycheck
to damn paycheck.

970
00:57:35,452 --> 00:57:36,851
What about the Mexico money?

971
00:57:36,886 --> 00:57:38,012
Poof.

972
00:57:41,591 --> 00:57:43,183
I'm livin' week to week...

973
00:57:45,228 --> 00:57:46,695
hand to damn mouth.

974
00:57:52,235 --> 00:57:53,497
Let me tell you something.

975
00:57:53,536 --> 00:57:55,401
That's the only way to live.

976
00:57:55,438 --> 00:57:57,303
Week to week, day to day...

977
00:57:57,340 --> 00:57:59,968
hour to hour, minute to minute.

978
00:58:00,977 --> 00:58:02,672
Each day in the moment, son.

979
00:58:04,314 --> 00:58:05,872
Enjoy the hell out of life.

980
00:58:08,117 --> 00:58:09,345
One day, you wake up...

981
00:58:11,788 --> 00:58:13,016
and it's gone.

982
00:59:38,474 --> 00:59:40,237
What happens if you're about
to lose everything...

983
00:59:40,276 --> 00:59:41,800
that's made you who you are?

984
00:59:43,246 --> 00:59:46,113
Your home, your teacher...

985
00:59:47,383 --> 00:59:48,714
your hopes and dreams?

986
00:59:50,253 --> 00:59:53,188
When that all goes,
what's left?

987
01:00:20,516 --> 01:00:22,507
I'm not sure
about the speaker system, Tom.

988
01:00:22,552 --> 01:00:24,543
I don't think
they have it anymore.

989
01:00:24,587 --> 01:00:26,214
Well, just ask him, Mom.

990
01:00:26,255 --> 01:00:27,517
Look, Ernie swears it's in
there...

991
01:00:27,557 --> 01:00:29,320
and he says he needs
it for the pageant.

992
01:00:29,359 --> 01:00:30,519
And you know how Ernie is.

993
01:00:30,560 --> 01:00:32,255
He's not gonna let me alone
until he gets an answer.

994
01:00:33,763 --> 01:00:34,752
Okay.

995
01:01:07,263 --> 01:01:09,322
Mom, what about the speaker?

996
01:01:09,365 --> 01:01:10,798
I couldn't ask him, Tom.

997
01:01:10,833 --> 01:01:11,891
Why not?

998
01:01:11,934 --> 01:01:13,834
Because I don't work there
anymore.

999
01:01:15,571 --> 01:01:16,731
What?

1000
01:01:16,773 --> 01:01:20,368
I got laid off in September.

1001
01:01:21,344 --> 01:01:22,936
Business was slow.

1002
01:01:22,979 --> 01:01:24,446
Oh, my God.

1003
01:01:25,815 --> 01:01:27,248
You should've told us.

1004
01:01:27,283 --> 01:01:28,807
No, I didn't wanna
worry you kids...

1005
01:01:28,851 --> 01:01:31,081
interfere with your school.

1006
01:01:31,120 --> 01:01:36,456
Mom, you come down here
every day, all day long.

1007
01:01:36,492 --> 01:01:39,154
No, I sit on the bench,
or I go over...

1008
01:01:39,195 --> 01:01:41,493
and I visit at the hospital,
or I, um...

1009
01:01:41,531 --> 01:01:42,964
I help out at the church.

1010
01:01:42,999 --> 01:01:49,336
And I look for work every day,
but there's nothing out there.

1011
01:01:52,308 --> 01:01:54,469
We're going to lose the house,
Tom.

1012
01:01:55,878 --> 01:01:56,867
We're gonna lose everything.

1013
01:01:56,913 --> 01:01:57,971
No.

1014
01:02:00,817 --> 01:02:03,445
No, Mom, hey, it'll be okay.

1015
01:02:03,486 --> 01:02:05,545
I'm not so sure anymore.

1016
01:02:07,023 --> 01:02:08,456
How will we live?

1017
01:02:10,560 --> 01:02:11,857
Oh, God.

1018
01:02:11,894 --> 01:02:13,293
I'll move.

1019
01:02:13,329 --> 01:02:16,230
I'll leave Placerville,
and I'll get a job in...

1020
01:02:16,265 --> 01:02:19,462
No. We'll figure it out, okay?

1021
01:02:19,502 --> 01:02:21,663
You have so many friends here
in town. They'll help.

1022
01:02:21,704 --> 01:02:23,262
- I'll go talk to everybody in
town.
- No!

1023
01:02:23,306 --> 01:02:25,001
No, you won't.

1024
01:02:25,041 --> 01:02:30,001
Maryanne Kinkade
does not ask for charity.

1025
01:02:30,046 --> 01:02:34,881
I couldn't endure the shame,
humiliation.

1026
01:02:36,018 --> 01:02:38,350
I will suffer this alone.

1027
01:02:39,589 --> 01:02:43,719
The last thing that I still have
that is mine is my pride.

1028
01:02:45,027 --> 01:02:46,460
You understand.

1029
01:03:04,280 --> 01:03:07,738
Shouldn't I be in the center,
and shouldn't I be bigger?

1030
01:03:07,784 --> 01:03:09,615
You're plenty big, Tanya.

1031
01:03:11,387 --> 01:03:13,116
Can you fix it?

1032
01:03:13,156 --> 01:03:14,919
I'll see what I can do.

1033
01:03:14,957 --> 01:03:16,822
And you messed up my nose.

1034
01:03:16,859 --> 01:03:18,554
I know, I hate that.

1035
01:03:18,594 --> 01:03:20,027
I love your nose.

1036
01:03:25,334 --> 01:03:26,665
Guess who.

1037
01:03:27,637 --> 01:03:29,400
Hey, you made it.

1038
01:03:32,942 --> 01:03:33,966
Well?

1039
01:03:36,879 --> 01:03:40,940
Well, it pays the rent, right?

1040
01:03:40,983 --> 01:03:43,451
All of a sudden,
Hope was there...

1041
01:03:43,486 --> 01:03:46,250
with all her big city dreams
for me...

1042
01:03:46,289 --> 01:03:49,281
and my two worlds collided.

1043
01:03:50,526 --> 01:03:52,721
Hey. Get ready to go.

1044
01:03:52,762 --> 01:03:55,128
That's it, that's it.
Smile. Smile.

1045
01:03:57,166 --> 01:04:00,294
Oh, that's it.
Oh, good. Okay.

1046
01:04:00,336 --> 01:04:02,201
This is so great.

1047
01:04:02,238 --> 01:04:03,535
Ernie, look this way.

1048
01:04:06,576 --> 01:04:08,771
Come on. That's it, That's it.

1049
01:04:08,811 --> 01:04:11,075
Oh, good, Cheryl.
Stand back there.

1050
01:04:13,049 --> 01:04:15,347
How'd the skank weasel her way
back in, Ernie?

1051
01:04:15,384 --> 01:04:16,476
What's she got on ya?

1052
01:04:16,519 --> 01:04:17,918
Nothing. Nothing!

1053
01:04:17,954 --> 01:04:19,353
Yeah, and if birds could fly.

1054
01:04:19,388 --> 01:04:22,016
Yes, birds can fly.

1055
01:04:22,058 --> 01:04:23,821
Suck an egg, '77.

1056
01:04:23,860 --> 01:04:25,828
Hey, come on, ladies.
Please, zip, zip.

1057
01:04:25,862 --> 01:04:27,261
All right.

1058
01:04:28,030 --> 01:04:29,930
And now from Placerville...

1059
01:04:29,966 --> 01:04:34,164
the official Christmas tree
capital of the world...

1060
01:04:35,471 --> 01:04:36,802
here to light
our town twee...

1061
01:04:37,974 --> 01:04:42,707
our town tree is a veteran
Miss Placerville.

1062
01:04:45,882 --> 01:04:49,682
So here she is now
to turn it on.

1063
01:04:51,520 --> 01:04:53,852
Hello, Sacramento.

1064
01:04:54,924 --> 01:05:00,157
I'm Tanya Kapinski,
Miss Placerville, 1974.

1065
01:05:00,196 --> 01:05:02,130
You know, I've worked
as a professional model...

1066
01:05:02,164 --> 01:05:03,426
for many years.

1067
01:05:03,466 --> 01:05:04,797
And in fact,
if you happen to have...

1068
01:05:04,834 --> 01:05:07,564
the April 1974 issue
of "Easy Rider"...

1069
01:05:07,603 --> 01:05:09,833
I'd be more than happy
to sign that for you...

1070
01:05:09,872 --> 01:05:12,170
- right after the ceremony.
- That's good, huh?

1071
01:05:15,645 --> 01:05:17,545
But there's no place like home.

1072
01:05:19,448 --> 01:05:23,407
I mean, really,
home is just the best place...

1073
01:05:23,452 --> 01:05:25,044
that a person could be from.

1074
01:05:27,723 --> 01:05:30,157
And so it is with my great
honor...

1075
01:05:30,192 --> 01:05:32,717
that I'm here to light up
Placerville...

1076
01:05:32,762 --> 01:05:35,526
the Christmas tree capital
of the world.

1077
01:05:39,302 --> 01:05:44,934
Okay, in five, four,
three, two, one.

1078
01:05:56,218 --> 01:05:57,048
What?

1079
01:06:00,823 --> 01:06:02,290
Just 'cause I wired it?

1080
01:06:03,459 --> 01:06:05,950
It wasn't my fault, okay?!

1081
01:06:21,277 --> 01:06:22,539
Nicole.

1082
01:06:30,953 --> 01:06:32,648
Give me your hand.

1083
01:06:36,659 --> 01:06:37,921
Hi, Glen.

1084
01:06:39,061 --> 01:06:40,119
It's me.

1085
01:06:42,465 --> 01:06:44,524
Sorry, I'm a little behind. I...

1086
01:06:45,968 --> 01:06:47,265
What a day.

1087
01:06:48,704 --> 01:06:50,797
There's a beautiful moon
coming up.

1088
01:06:53,075 --> 01:06:55,976
A crescent moon for Christmas.

1089
01:06:57,346 --> 01:06:58,438
I brought you something.

1090
01:06:58,481 --> 01:07:00,608
It's icy on the bridge.

1091
01:07:03,986 --> 01:07:05,385
Don't fall.

1092
01:07:10,760 --> 01:07:13,388
Your fingers in mine, Nicole.

1093
01:07:16,766 --> 01:07:19,064
It's Maryanne.

1094
01:07:19,101 --> 01:07:21,262
I brought you
some hot chocolate, Glen.

1095
01:07:21,303 --> 01:07:24,238
I don't want to lose you.

1096
01:07:26,342 --> 01:07:28,537
Give me your hand.

1097
01:07:28,577 --> 01:07:30,101
Here, let me help you up.

1098
01:07:30,146 --> 01:07:32,740
Stubborn woman.

1099
01:07:35,051 --> 01:07:36,416
Lean on me.

1100
01:07:39,789 --> 01:07:42,417
We'll cross the Pont Neuf.

1101
01:07:44,693 --> 01:07:49,323
Glen, we're not in Paris.

1102
01:07:50,299 --> 01:07:51,823
We're in your studio.

1103
01:07:59,108 --> 01:08:00,439
My studio?

1104
01:08:04,413 --> 01:08:06,540
My easel, my paints?

1105
01:08:08,117 --> 01:08:09,277
They're all here.

1106
01:08:14,356 --> 01:08:15,823
Nicole?

1107
01:08:19,095 --> 01:08:22,189
It's 1977, Glen.

1108
01:08:30,539 --> 01:08:32,973
You've made me an old man.

1109
01:08:34,910 --> 01:08:37,310
I was young a moment ago.

1110
01:08:46,555 --> 01:08:49,547
Here, look at this.

1111
01:08:54,096 --> 01:08:55,393
Smell this.

1112
01:08:57,233 --> 01:08:58,564
Isn't it beautiful?

1113
01:09:00,503 --> 01:09:02,698
Let me take you on a walk.

1114
01:09:02,738 --> 01:09:06,538
You haven't been outside in...
in weeks.

1115
01:09:07,343 --> 01:09:08,503
Let me take you on a walk.

1116
01:09:08,544 --> 01:09:11,172
Let me take you
to the Christmas pageant.

1117
01:09:12,448 --> 01:09:15,246
I respectfully decline
your invitation.

1118
01:09:15,284 --> 01:09:18,879
My next visit to the church
will be for my funeral.

1119
01:09:20,656 --> 01:09:24,092
There's still life
out there for you, Glen.

1120
01:09:24,126 --> 01:09:26,924
You need to touch it
and taste it and see it.

1121
01:09:26,962 --> 01:09:29,294
I see more than you think.

1122
01:09:31,500 --> 01:09:37,905
Maryanne, you're killing
yourself with pride.

1123
01:10:25,221 --> 01:10:28,918
That night, Placerville
had its chance to redeem itself.

1124
01:10:29,792 --> 01:10:31,555
The Christmas pageant
seemed like a sure thing.

1125
01:10:31,594 --> 01:10:33,994
I mean,
how can you go wrong...

1126
01:10:34,029 --> 01:10:36,793
with little kids
and some wise men?

1127
01:10:36,832 --> 01:10:39,801
I figured wax-based paint would
really make the scenery shine...

1128
01:10:39,835 --> 01:10:41,666
under the TV lights.

1129
01:10:52,615 --> 01:10:54,207
Showtime.

1130
01:11:04,193 --> 01:11:07,356
"And it came to pass
in those days...

1131
01:11:07,396 --> 01:11:10,593
"that there went out a decree
from Caesar Augustus...

1132
01:11:10,633 --> 01:11:13,033
"that all the world
should be taxed.

1133
01:11:13,068 --> 01:11:18,597
"And Joseph went up from Galilee
into Bethlehem with Mary...

1134
01:11:18,641 --> 01:11:20,404
"his espoused wife.

1135
01:11:25,147 --> 01:11:28,173
"And she brought forth
their firstborn son...

1136
01:11:29,385 --> 01:11:31,353
"and she wrapped him
in swaddling clothes...

1137
01:11:31,387 --> 01:11:32,877
"and laid him in a manger...

1138
01:11:32,921 --> 01:11:35,583
"for there was no room
for them at the inn."

1139
01:11:56,045 --> 01:11:57,034
What's wrong?

1140
01:12:00,549 --> 01:12:01,914
What's happening
to the scenery?

1141
01:12:04,186 --> 01:12:06,848
Oh, my God.

1142
01:12:06,889 --> 01:12:09,153
We must've used too much wax.

1143
01:12:10,993 --> 01:12:12,392
Under these lights...

1144
01:12:12,428 --> 01:12:13,417
It's melting.

1145
01:12:15,397 --> 01:12:16,864
Oh, look, the donkey's peeing.

1146
01:12:23,038 --> 01:12:28,442
"And, um, there were in that
same country shepherds"...

1147
01:12:30,546 --> 01:12:32,070
That's not good. That's not...

1148
01:12:32,114 --> 01:12:34,139
"watching over their flock."

1149
01:12:40,522 --> 01:12:42,752
Stop laughing.

1150
01:12:42,791 --> 01:12:45,988
Oh, well, looks I'm gonna be
on riot control any minute.

1151
01:12:46,662 --> 01:12:48,152
Let's walk off.
Come on, Sweetie.

1152
01:12:48,197 --> 01:12:49,721
Let's walk.

1153
01:12:49,765 --> 01:12:51,232
No, no, no.
What are you doing?

1154
01:12:51,266 --> 01:12:52,631
No, no, no. Mary, sit down.

1155
01:12:52,668 --> 01:12:53,930
What's going on?

1156
01:12:53,969 --> 01:12:56,199
No, no, no, no, no,
don't stop the show.

1157
01:12:56,238 --> 01:12:57,262
It is not the end
of the world.

1158
01:12:57,306 --> 01:12:58,330
Yes, it is the end of the world.

1159
01:12:58,374 --> 01:12:59,671
You don't understand.

1160
01:12:59,708 --> 01:13:02,302
This was supposed to be
a beautiful Christmas pageant.

1161
01:13:02,378 --> 01:13:03,675
It was supposed
to be a light, airy...

1162
01:13:03,712 --> 01:13:04,644
Get back there.

1163
01:13:05,314 --> 01:13:07,441
There was supposed to be
a lighted Christmas tree...

1164
01:13:07,483 --> 01:13:08,745
in the town square.

1165
01:13:11,687 --> 01:13:12,676
No.

1166
01:13:12,721 --> 01:13:14,416
Huh, great.

1167
01:13:14,456 --> 01:13:16,651
And now the final humiliation.

1168
01:13:16,692 --> 01:13:18,683
Thank you, Tommy.
Thank you.

1169
01:13:18,727 --> 01:13:19,887
This is all your fault.

1170
01:13:19,928 --> 01:13:21,862
For goodness sake.

1171
01:13:21,897 --> 01:13:23,865
You don't have
to listen to this, Thomas.

1172
01:13:23,899 --> 01:13:24,888
Let's get out of here...

1173
01:13:24,933 --> 01:13:26,161
back to where
they appreciate you.

1174
01:13:26,201 --> 01:13:27,998
Oh! Oh, wonderful.

1175
01:13:28,036 --> 01:13:30,664
Okay. Well, the TV people
are packing it in...

1176
01:13:30,706 --> 01:13:33,641
and, great,
the audience is leaving, too.

1177
01:13:33,675 --> 01:13:35,734
Well, Tommy,
you painted the scenery.

1178
01:13:35,778 --> 01:13:37,678
You're the one that screwed up!

1179
01:13:37,713 --> 01:13:39,078
Now, now.
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

1180
01:13:39,114 --> 01:13:41,014
Just cool your jets there,
Captain Kangaroo...

1181
01:13:41,049 --> 01:13:42,038
and back off.

1182
01:13:43,452 --> 01:13:45,352
Tommy Boy didn't screw this up.

1183
01:13:46,522 --> 01:13:49,889
He gave this town
a great Christmas gift.

1184
01:13:51,493 --> 01:13:53,393
Look at that mural.

1185
01:13:53,429 --> 01:13:56,626
He gave you the heart
and soul of this place.

1186
01:13:58,400 --> 01:14:00,891
Yeah, it looks
pretty good to me.

1187
01:14:04,373 --> 01:14:06,000
This old town...

1188
01:14:06,041 --> 01:14:08,339
you don't need
to impress anyone.

1189
01:14:09,578 --> 01:14:12,513
You're A-okay
just the way you are.

1190
01:14:14,716 --> 01:14:16,445
Aren't we all here
celebrating...

1191
01:14:16,485 --> 01:14:18,578
someone who was born
in a garage?

1192
01:14:18,620 --> 01:14:19,746
Stable.

1193
01:14:19,788 --> 01:14:20,914
Or a...

1194
01:14:20,956 --> 01:14:21,980
- Stable.
- Stable.

1195
01:14:22,024 --> 01:14:23,013
Stable?

1196
01:14:25,494 --> 01:14:27,519
He never had much money, either.

1197
01:14:29,364 --> 01:14:31,457
Thank you.
Thank you for your time.

1198
01:14:34,570 --> 01:14:35,935
Thanks, Dad.

1199
01:14:41,376 --> 01:14:42,365
We'd love to share...

1200
01:14:42,411 --> 01:14:45,278
our Christmas candle lighting
ceremony with you.

1201
01:14:45,314 --> 01:14:47,009
The children are ready.

1202
01:14:47,049 --> 01:14:48,038
Come on, children.

1203
01:14:48,083 --> 01:14:49,380
Let me help with you that,
darlin'.

1204
01:14:50,319 --> 01:14:51,445
Hope.

1205
01:14:56,191 --> 01:14:57,988
You don't belong here.

1206
01:14:59,695 --> 01:15:01,253
I don't know where I belong.

1207
01:15:01,296 --> 01:15:03,730
Don't give up on yourself.

1208
01:15:03,765 --> 01:15:05,392
I'm not giving up.

1209
01:15:29,625 --> 01:15:31,616
Will you read, Maryanne?

1210
01:15:43,605 --> 01:15:51,444
"For unto us a child is born,
unto us a son is given.

1211
01:15:53,615 --> 01:15:56,516
"And the government
shall be upon his shoulder...

1212
01:15:57,853 --> 01:16:01,812
"and his name shall be called
Wonderful, Counselor...

1213
01:16:02,824 --> 01:16:06,590
"the Mighty God,
the Everlasting Father...

1214
01:16:08,030 --> 01:16:09,327
"the Prince of Peace."

1215
01:16:15,470 --> 01:16:18,530
You know, I don't know a lot
about scripture.

1216
01:16:18,574 --> 01:16:22,806
I'm not a scholar,
and I'm not a preacher...

1217
01:16:24,980 --> 01:16:26,880
but when I look out
and I see the faces...

1218
01:16:26,915 --> 01:16:29,816
of these young children
in the candlelight...

1219
01:16:30,886 --> 01:16:32,820
so full of hope...

1220
01:16:33,622 --> 01:16:37,319
I feel the presence
of God right here...

1221
01:16:38,727 --> 01:16:43,528
like little angels
telling us all...

1222
01:16:43,565 --> 01:16:47,831
to, "Fear not, I bring you
tidings of great joy."

1223
01:16:49,705 --> 01:16:54,199
You are the light of the world
in a...

1224
01:16:56,011 --> 01:16:57,410
a very dark winter.

1225
01:16:58,947 --> 01:17:03,441
And we could all use a little
bit of extra light right now.

1226
01:17:11,293 --> 01:17:12,521
Excuse me, angel.

1227
01:17:21,269 --> 01:17:25,365
I light this candle as a symbol
of sharing God's love...

1228
01:17:25,407 --> 01:17:27,432
with all of his children.

1229
01:17:30,779 --> 01:17:35,648
That Christmas Eve, I realized
that in a vast, black night...

1230
01:17:35,684 --> 01:17:37,879
even a little light
shines brightly...

1231
01:17:37,919 --> 01:17:41,821
and all we can do is
our best to find that light...

1232
01:17:41,857 --> 01:17:43,620
and share it with others.

1233
01:17:45,460 --> 01:17:46,449
Ernie.

1234
01:17:58,407 --> 01:18:00,034
Okay. And...

1235
01:18:27,736 --> 01:18:28,930
Merry Christmas.

1236
01:18:30,172 --> 01:18:31,799
Happy holidays.

1237
01:18:32,941 --> 01:18:34,203
Bless you.

1238
01:20:05,333 --> 01:20:06,698
It's Christmas Eve, Glen.

1239
01:20:09,838 --> 01:20:10,930
How are you?

1240
01:20:28,223 --> 01:20:29,281
Remember when you told me...

1241
01:20:29,324 --> 01:20:31,758
this was the one night of the
year when animals could talk?

1242
01:20:38,033 --> 01:20:41,901
You said when the animals talk,
it wasn't magic.

1243
01:20:44,973 --> 01:20:46,167
It was holy...

1244
01:20:48,610 --> 01:20:50,100
a glimpse of the sacred.

1245
01:20:54,616 --> 01:20:57,141
You said it was a moment
where we could understand...

1246
01:20:57,185 --> 01:20:58,982
the heart of every living thing.

1247
01:21:05,594 --> 01:21:06,822
I always thought
it was a miracle...

1248
01:21:06,862 --> 01:21:09,228
when you built your studio
in the field by my house.

1249
01:21:11,800 --> 01:21:15,998
It was like God's gift to me,
bringing you here.

1250
01:21:19,474 --> 01:21:21,908
You always told me you weren't
gonna teach me how to paint...

1251
01:21:24,212 --> 01:21:25,509
but why to paint.

1252
01:21:30,051 --> 01:21:32,451
And I'll be forever grateful
to you for that.

1253
01:21:36,424 --> 01:21:38,221
I wish I could give you back
something...

1254
01:21:45,033 --> 01:21:46,694
but I have nothing.

1255
01:21:50,472 --> 01:21:52,201
We're losing the cottage, Glen.

1256
01:21:55,744 --> 01:21:58,178
A year from now, I have no idea
where we'll be.

1257
01:22:02,684 --> 01:22:04,242
This may be
our last Christmas together...

1258
01:22:04,286 --> 01:22:06,117
and I have no gift for you,
Glen.

1259
01:22:09,257 --> 01:22:11,555
I have no way to thank you
for everything.

1260
01:22:14,863 --> 01:22:17,195
No money, nothing.

1261
01:22:21,369 --> 01:22:22,563
Just love.

1262
01:22:28,043 --> 01:22:29,533
I love you, Glen.

1263
01:22:33,114 --> 01:22:36,413
Don't give up, please.

1264
01:22:36,451 --> 01:22:37,577
That's the first thing
you taught me...

1265
01:22:37,619 --> 01:22:40,349
about being an artist:
you never give up.

1266
01:22:40,388 --> 01:22:42,322
Don't give up, Glen.

1267
01:22:45,293 --> 01:22:47,318
There's a light in you still.

1268
01:24:41,042 --> 01:24:43,033
The snow stopped falling
by Christmas morning.

1269
01:24:44,145 --> 01:24:45,476
It had blanketed Placerville...

1270
01:24:45,513 --> 01:24:46,537
Thank you.

1271
01:24:46,581 --> 01:24:50,608
deep and crisp and even.

1272
01:24:50,652 --> 01:24:51,710
Now it's your turn.

1273
01:24:52,854 --> 01:24:54,617
There you go. Open it up.

1274
01:25:05,333 --> 01:25:06,391
Thank you, Tom.

1275
01:25:08,136 --> 01:25:10,161
Now I have the cottage forever.

1276
01:25:21,416 --> 01:25:22,576
No, no, no, no, no.

1277
01:25:22,617 --> 01:25:24,278
Don't say no, Mom.

1278
01:25:25,220 --> 01:25:27,552
It's not much, but it's a start
of a new life for us.

1279
01:25:31,392 --> 01:25:32,689
We gotta stick together.

1280
01:25:35,630 --> 01:25:36,688
We're all we've got.

1281
01:25:38,366 --> 01:25:39,355
Thank you, Pat.

1282
01:25:40,568 --> 01:25:41,626
Thank you.

1283
01:25:43,838 --> 01:25:45,829
It looks
like a million dollars to me.

1284
01:25:53,815 --> 01:25:54,804
Good morning.

1285
01:25:56,784 --> 01:25:58,979
We've come to help you
fix this place up.

1286
01:25:59,020 --> 01:26:01,648
Then maybe you could sell it.

1287
01:26:01,689 --> 01:26:04,954
It's about time somebody
gave you a gift for Christmas.

1288
01:26:06,261 --> 01:26:07,523
But how did everybody know?

1289
01:26:10,231 --> 01:26:11,425
I spilled the beans.

1290
01:26:13,001 --> 01:26:15,629
We know this probably
won't solve all your problems...

1291
01:26:15,670 --> 01:26:17,968
but we had to do something.

1292
01:26:19,073 --> 01:26:20,438
It was kind of my idea.

1293
01:26:20,475 --> 01:26:23,410
I mean,
after all you've done for us.

1294
01:26:23,444 --> 01:26:25,935
Maryanne, for you.

1295
01:26:25,980 --> 01:26:28,471
For good fortune and happiness.

1296
01:26:29,551 --> 01:26:31,280
I don't know what to say.

1297
01:26:32,654 --> 01:26:34,246
Say merry Christmas.

1298
01:26:36,658 --> 01:26:37,647
Merry Christmas.

1299
01:26:46,000 --> 01:26:48,161
Okay, son,
that ought to do it.

1300
01:26:48,203 --> 01:26:49,329
Let's give her a shot.

1301
01:26:51,973 --> 01:26:53,634
All right, come on, baby.

1302
01:26:53,675 --> 01:26:56,439
Come on now! Come to Big Bill.

1303
01:26:56,477 --> 01:26:58,877
Start that truck!

1304
01:26:58,913 --> 01:27:00,107
Attaboy.

1305
01:27:02,383 --> 01:27:05,477
Please sweep the dust back in.

1306
01:27:05,520 --> 01:27:06,782
What?

1307
01:27:06,821 --> 01:27:10,382
You are sweeping the good luck
out of the house.

1308
01:27:10,425 --> 01:27:11,653
Let go of broom. Go, go.

1309
01:27:13,695 --> 01:27:15,856
Yes. Do it. Do it.

1310
01:27:15,897 --> 01:27:17,159
Very good. Yeah.

1311
01:27:25,506 --> 01:27:26,803
I never knew.

1312
01:27:28,610 --> 01:27:30,043
Knew what?

1313
01:27:31,479 --> 01:27:32,878
That you matter to everyone?

1314
01:27:38,253 --> 01:27:39,413
Well, you do.

1315
01:28:09,050 --> 01:28:11,041
Tom, can you get that, please?

1316
01:28:17,625 --> 01:28:19,092
Glen, what are you...

1317
01:28:19,127 --> 01:28:20,424
Come here. Come in.
Oh, my God.

1318
01:28:20,461 --> 01:28:21,450
What are you doing here?

1319
01:28:21,496 --> 01:28:23,020
How'd you get over here?

1320
01:28:23,064 --> 01:28:24,224
My staff.

1321
01:28:25,933 --> 01:28:27,127
My rod.

1322
01:28:27,168 --> 01:28:28,726
Are you okay?

1323
01:28:28,770 --> 01:28:33,969
It's the light, Tom,
that's what lasts.

1324
01:28:34,008 --> 01:28:36,636
The leaves are transient.

1325
01:28:36,678 --> 01:28:40,774
They grow, turn green,
turn red, and die...

1326
01:28:40,815 --> 01:28:45,582
but behind them,
the light lasts forever.

1327
01:28:45,620 --> 01:28:47,986
Glen, please, come sit down.

1328
01:28:48,022 --> 01:28:50,582
Paint the light.

1329
01:28:54,962 --> 01:28:56,554
Christmas gift.

1330
01:28:58,199 --> 01:29:04,570
Remember how Sidney hoped
I had one more painting in me?

1331
01:29:05,973 --> 01:29:07,201
I did.

1332
01:29:08,976 --> 01:29:10,204
Just one.

1333
01:29:25,860 --> 01:29:26,952
Latin.

1334
01:29:27,995 --> 01:29:29,656
Good old Latin.

1335
01:29:30,898 --> 01:29:32,525
"The Last Leaf"...

1336
01:29:35,169 --> 01:29:37,160
is my last painting, Tom.

1337
01:29:40,274 --> 01:29:43,368
No, Glen, no.

1338
01:29:43,411 --> 01:29:47,211
I had been trying
to paint my sorrow...

1339
01:29:47,248 --> 01:29:50,581
to show the bleakness of a world
without Nicole.

1340
01:29:51,419 --> 01:29:55,253
But then you came
with a candle last night...

1341
01:29:55,289 --> 01:29:59,953
and I knew what
Nicole's memorial should be.

1342
01:29:59,994 --> 01:30:04,328
Not darkness, no, but light.

1343
01:30:07,402 --> 01:30:12,965
Sometimes we can barely see
beyond the forest to the sky.

1344
01:30:14,876 --> 01:30:17,845
I was painting the leaves
of the forest...

1345
01:30:17,879 --> 01:30:21,212
and never saw the light
of the sky behind it.

1346
01:30:22,984 --> 01:30:24,679
Now I see it.

1347
01:30:28,489 --> 01:30:31,390
That's all I need to see now.

1348
01:30:33,161 --> 01:30:34,822
I'll treasure this forever,
Glen.

1349
01:30:34,862 --> 01:30:36,386
No, you will not.

1350
01:30:36,431 --> 01:30:37,989
You will take it
to Sidney Marvin...

1351
01:30:38,032 --> 01:30:39,056
and you will sell it.

1352
01:30:39,100 --> 01:30:44,060
The last Glen Wesman
should bring you enough...

1353
01:30:44,105 --> 01:30:46,972
to keep this cottage forever.

1354
01:30:47,008 --> 01:30:49,306
Oh, Glen. Thank you.

1355
01:30:51,512 --> 01:30:54,709
No, thank you. Thank you.

1356
01:30:54,749 --> 01:30:56,444
What for?

1357
01:30:58,986 --> 01:31:03,389
You managed to put Humpty-Dumpty
back together again.

1358
01:31:29,083 --> 01:31:31,916
Those were the last brushstrokes
Glen ever painted.

1359
01:31:33,221 --> 01:31:35,314
He sat at our table
for Christmas dinner.

1360
01:31:38,459 --> 01:31:40,427
- There, Tom. You'll carve it.
- Of course.

1361
01:31:43,464 --> 01:31:44,658
All right.

1362
01:31:50,171 --> 01:31:52,298
Holy Father,
bless this meal...

1363
01:31:52,340 --> 01:31:55,400
and all who are gathered here.
Amen.

1364
01:31:56,677 --> 01:31:57,666
Merry Christmas.

1365
01:31:59,046 --> 01:32:00,638
Merry Christmas, Glen.

1366
01:32:32,313 --> 01:32:35,510
My mother made sure
Glen was well-fed.

1367
01:32:35,550 --> 01:32:37,575
After dinner, we sang carols.

1368
01:32:38,486 --> 01:32:41,046
The old favorites,
with words like...

1369
01:32:41,088 --> 01:32:43,579
"the hopes and fears
of all the years"...

1370
01:32:43,624 --> 01:32:47,060
and "God rest ye merry,
gentlemen."

1371
01:32:52,166 --> 01:32:53,963
Then I helped Glen walk home.

1372
01:32:59,140 --> 01:33:00,573
Big Jim stayed up all night...

1373
01:33:00,608 --> 01:33:02,439
fixing the wiring
on that tree...

1374
01:33:02,476 --> 01:33:05,240
and Placerville turned on
its real lights that year.

1375
01:33:06,213 --> 01:33:08,113
I always thought it was the year
we found Christmas...

1376
01:33:08,149 --> 01:33:09,138
all over again.

1377
01:33:21,996 --> 01:33:23,258
Wow.

1378
01:33:34,542 --> 01:33:36,703
When I went to see Glen
the next evening...

1379
01:33:38,679 --> 01:33:40,613
he had gone home for good.

1380
01:33:42,083 --> 01:33:44,278
He was back where the light
burns brighter...

1381
01:33:45,486 --> 01:33:47,750
than we could ever imagine.

1382
01:33:47,788 --> 01:33:48,914
<i>Pacem,</i> Glen.

1383
01:33:49,991 --> 01:33:51,117
Peace.

1384
01:33:52,760 --> 01:33:54,193
You showed me the light...

1385
01:33:55,196 --> 01:33:57,460
a light that has filled my life
ever since.

1386
01:33:57,498 --> 01:34:03,095
You have that power holding
the whole world together.

1387
01:34:06,107 --> 01:34:08,200
Now I see it.

1388
01:34:13,314 --> 01:34:14,542
That was thirty years ago.

1389
01:34:16,250 --> 01:34:21,950
Today, Big Jim still puts up
just one star, nothing else.

1390
01:34:23,391 --> 01:34:26,792
And he and the Gundersons
finally became friends.

1391
01:34:27,895 --> 01:34:30,557
Vesta's buried in that
little cemetery near our house.

1392
01:34:31,565 --> 01:34:33,624
Butch is there, too...

1393
01:34:33,668 --> 01:34:36,000
finally resting peacefully
next to his son.

1394
01:34:37,605 --> 01:34:39,368
Glen's painting
took a journey, too...

1395
01:34:40,007 --> 01:34:42,134
and is now owned
by a museum in New York.

1396
01:34:44,045 --> 01:34:48,448
Mr. Rosa retired, but he still
keeps track of all of our lives.

1397
01:34:48,482 --> 01:34:52,248
Tanya kept entering
the Miss Placerville contest...

1398
01:34:52,286 --> 01:34:54,686
until she was well into her 50s.

1399
01:34:54,722 --> 01:35:00,354
And to this day, Ernie still
promotes Placerville... quietly.

1400
01:35:01,629 --> 01:35:02,823
Pat stuck with his schooling...

1401
01:35:02,863 --> 01:35:05,161
and became a well-known writer
and professor.

1402
01:35:06,400 --> 01:35:07,424
Nanette?

1403
01:35:08,502 --> 01:35:11,494
Well, that's a story
for another day.

1404
01:35:13,574 --> 01:35:16,475
And Mom,
thanks to Glen's gift of love...

1405
01:35:17,545 --> 01:35:20,639
well, she never had to worry
about a mortgage payment again.

1406
01:35:20,681 --> 01:35:22,911
She got a job she loved
with the county...

1407
01:35:22,950 --> 01:35:24,747
and retired several years later.

1408
01:35:26,487 --> 01:35:27,647
And Bill?

1409
01:35:29,423 --> 01:35:32,881
Well, my dad
kept leading his crazy life...

1410
01:35:32,927 --> 01:35:35,828
driving his old heap
in search of new adventures.

1411
01:35:41,302 --> 01:35:44,669
As for me,
I'm still trying my best...

1412
01:35:44,705 --> 01:35:46,605
to use the lessons Glen
taught me.

1413
01:35:47,708 --> 01:35:53,669
Lessons about art, about life,
and about light.

1414
01:35:55,382 --> 01:36:01,007
In the end, love is the
brightest light of all.

1415
01:36:10,231 --> 01:36:17,034
FOR GLEN

